yarp - it's in there.

so after extensive goldfishing analysis of Z&O, here are my findings:
 - the thing is super mana hungry, even after having like 16 mana rocks.
 - I need to pretty much cut all cards at cmc 5+. They were so clunky to play because i want to play Okaun first, then next turn I'm going to play Zndrsplt. 
 - I stayed away from mana rocks like Worn Powerstone and Thran Dynamo because they didn't ramp into Okaun faster really. However, I found myself wanting to cast Zndrsplt AND have mana to equip Okaun with something in the same turn. So I'm going to put those heavier mana rocks in there.
 - I need more protection for Okaun, I felt too often a well-timed StP would hose me. Already have Greaves & Swiftfoot boots & Feast/Famine... not sure what else to add
 - Similar to above, I think I might want to add a couple of counterspells to protect Okaun. I'm playing Pact of Negation and Mana Drain but nothing else. Probably OG counterspell needs to go in. Considering Cryptic Command since it cal also tap down creatures or bounce stuff. Swan Song is questionable because it'll create a chump blocker for them.
 - I found Okaun very often getting to 48 power. I'm going to add Fling in there.
any suggestions appreciated!! ^
